headline: Alaska Airlines CEO expects full-year profit despite pricing struggles
summary: NEW DELHI (Reuters) -Alaska Airlines CEO Ben Minicucci said the company's pricing power has not recovered yet even as its bookings have stabilised following economic uncertainty that led to volatility in the first quarter.  Still, Minicucci said the company expects to report a profit this year.  Like most U.S. airlines, Alaska pulled its full-year financial forecast in April as President Donald Trump's trade war created the biggest uncertainty for the industry since the COVID-19 pandemic.
